SIMPLE: bundling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: bundling
<hw>bundling</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a former custom,
especially in New England, in which unmarried couples occupied the same
bed without undressing, especially during courtship. See
<er>bundle{2}</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the act of binding something into a
bundle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>the act of shoving hastily; <as>as, she complained
about <ex>bundling</ex> the children off to school</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bundobust</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
